Manages the Security Center Assessment Metadata for Azure Security Center.

> **NOTE:** This resource has been deprecated in favour of the `azure.securitycenter.AssessmentPolicy` resource and will be removed in the next major version of the AzureRM Provider. The new resource shares the same fields as this one, and information on migrating across can be found in this guide.

<a href="#state_threats_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">threats</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">Sequence[str]</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}A list of the threat impacts for the Security Center Assessment. Possible values are `AccountBreach`, `DataExfiltration`, `DataSpillage`, `DenialOfService`, `ElevationOfPrivilege`, `MaliciousInsider`, `MissingCoverage` and `ThreatResistance`.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_user_impact_python">
<a href="#state_user_impact_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">user_<wbr>impact</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">str</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The user impact of the Security Center Assessment. Possible values are `Low`, `Moderate` and `High`.
{{% /md %}}</dd></dl>
{{% /choosable %}}





## Import


Security Assessments Metadata can be imported using the `resource id`, e.g.

```sh
 $ pulumi import azure:securitycenter/assessmentMetadata:AssessmentMetadata example /subscriptions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/providers/Microsoft.Security/assessmentMetadata/metadata1
```
